What you need to know:  Kenya first took part in Summer Deaflympics in 1997 in Copenhagen, Denmark.Since then, Kenya has bagged a total of 38 medals; 12 gold, 10 silver and 16 bronze in the competition.In the last edition held in 2017 in Sumsun, Turkey, Kenya finished ninth overall and first in Africa with a total of 13 medals, four gold, four silver and six bronze.